TY  - JOUR
AU  - Ahn, Dong-Hyun
AU  - Conrad, Jennifer
AU  - Dittmar, Robert F.
T1  - Risk Adjustment and Trading Strategies
PY  - 2003
Y1  - 2003/04/01
DO  - 10.1093/rfs/hhg001
JO  - The Review of Financial Studies
JA  - Rev Financ Stud
VL  - 16
IS  - 2
SP  - 459
EP  - 485
SN  - 0893-9454
AB  - We assess the profitability of momentum strategies using a stochastic discount factor approach. In unconditional tests, approximately half of the strategies' profitability is explained. In conditional tests we see a further slight decline in profits. We argue that the risk of these strategies should be increasing in the market risk premium. Empirically, while their risk measures estimated relative to the stochastic discount factor behave as predicted, market betas do not; thus capital asset pricing model (CAPM)-like benchmarks may lead to incorrect inferences. Given that our nonparametric risk adjustment explains roughly half of momentum strategy profits, we cannot rule out the possibility of residual mispricing.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rfs/hhg001
ER  - 



